metadata.recording_metadata_summary: This recording is from a middle-school participating in the PLUS tutoring program. This school is called Jackson. Students in this school use iPads to access Zoom and generally use the math software IXL. The teacher in the classroom is named Bleacher & Co., although other teachers may be present. The tutor assigned to this classroom is named Suhyun Baik, although other tutors may be present.

events.description: Tutor and student sit silently waiting for audio connection.
Student looks around the classroom; loud background chatter is audible.

events.text: Okay, I'm Suzie. I'll be your tutor for today.
Um, do you mind sharing your screen and, um, showing me what you were solving for the math problems?
You look like a ton of snot just came out your nose.

events.description: Student starts screen sharing.
Zoom notification 'You are sharing your screen' appears.

events.details: Student swipes left on iOS home screen to change page.
Opens folder containing IXL
Opens IXL app

events.description: IXL question loads: 'What are the coordinates of the blue pentagon?'

events.text: It's yours! Not yours, it's yours!

events.details: Taps to enter text

Types 6

events.text: I don't know why we're talking. Unfortunately IXL does not require talking.

events.text: Okay, I'm gonna go check on other students but keep sharing your screen and solving the problems and I'll come back.
Please let me know if you have any questions.
